132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 424
H.P. 278 House of Representatives, February 4, 2025
An Act Concerning the Concealed Carrying of a Handgun by an
Individual Who Is 18 Years of Age but Under 21 Years of Age
Reference to the Committee on Judiciary suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative COLLINS of Sidney.
Cosponsored by Representative POIRIER of Skowhegan and
Representatives: FLYNN of Albion, GRIFFIN of Levant, GUERRETTE of Caribou,
HAGGAN of Hampden, MCINTYRE of Lowell, SMITH of Palermo, THORNE of Carmel,
Senator: HAGGAN of Penobscot.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §2001-A, sub-§2, ¶A-1, as enacted by PL 2015, c. 327, §2, is
3 amended to read:
4 A-1. A handgun carried by a person who is 21 18 years of age or older and is not
5 otherwise prohibited from carrying a firearm or is 18 years of age or older and under
6 21 years of age and is on active duty in the Armed Forces of the United States or the
7 National Guard or is an honorably discharged veteran of the Armed Forces of the
8 United States or the National Guard and is not otherwise prohibited from carrying a
9 firearm;
10 SUMMARY
1111 This bill removes the exception from the provisions of the Maine Revised Statutes,
1122 Title 25, section 2001-A concerning the carrying of concealed weapons for handguns
1133 carried by persons 18 years of age or older and under 21 years of age who are on active
1144 duty in the Armed Forces of the United States or the National Guard or who are honorably
1155 discharged veterans and allows a person who is 18 years of age or older who is not
1166 otherwise prohibited from carrying a firearm to carry a concealed handgun.
